Title: Second Quantization of the Dirac Equation in Cylindrical Coordinates  
Author: A.B. Balantekin and A.J. DeWeerd 
Address: Madison, Wisconsin 53706 USA  
Affiliation: Department of Physics, University of Wisconsin,  
Abstract: Cylindrical solutions of the Dirac equation have been studied as well as used in a variety of application. However, little attention has been paid to the second quantization in these coordinates. We present a procedure for second quantization which will allow the use of the Fock space formalism in the description of problems with the appropriate symmetry. 
