Reference-contexts: VII. CONCLUSIONS We have presented a procedure for second quantizing the Dirac equation in cylindrical coordinates. Previously, a method has been given for calculating pair production for homogeneous, time-dependent fields <ref> [13] </ref>. The above results can be used to extend this to a cylindrical region with MIT boundary conditions. This yields the same discretization of the transverse momentum as previous works [4-6], but also allows for the calculations with time-dependent fields.
